- 1.0.5 | Apr 05 2026:

  [Fix] _alert_slack_post_message: JSON-escape channel value before awk
      interpolation; prevents JSON injection from channel names containing
      double quotes or backslashes (mirrors _alert_slack_upload pattern)
  [Fix] _alert_email_local: defense-in-depth CR/LF stripping on all header
      values (recip, subject, from, reply-to); prevents header injection if
      called outside _alert_deliver_email
  [Fix] _alert_slack_upload: validate upload_url is HTTPS before uploading
      file content; rejects http, file, ftp, and empty URL schemes
  [Fix] _alert_slack_upload: use --data-urlencode for filename parameter in
      getUploadURLExternal; prevents form parameter injection from filenames
      containing & or other special characters
  [New] Tests for channel JSON-escape injection, email header CR/LF stripping,
      Slack upload URL HTTPS validation, filename URL-encoding
  [Fix] _alert_deliver_email: defense-in-depth CR/LF stripping on reply-to,
      recip, and from in relay path; parity with _alert_email_local
  [Fix] _alert_slack_upload: case-insensitive HTTPS validation on upload URL;
      extended case pattern for bash 4.1 compatibility (${var,,} prohibited)
  [New] Test for relay path Reply-To CR/LF stripping
  [Change] tests/infra: batsman 1.0.3 → 1.4.0 — file-group test splitting,
      GNU parallel on all 9 base images, grep -F fix in batsman_clean()

- 1.0.5 | Mar 23 2026:

  [Change] README: restructure to rfxn documentation convention floor level;
      add numbered sections (## 1. through ## 12.), centered badge row with
      flat-square style, bold one-liner, copyright blockquote, ## Support section

- 1.0.5 | Mar 16 2026:

  [Fix] All rm -f calls use 'command rm -f' to bypass potential user aliases
      on target systems; 17 instances across all delivery and cleanup paths
  [Fix] _alert_slack_upload: JSON-escape $channels and $file_id in
      completeUploadExternal request body; prevents malformed JSON from
      channel names containing special characters
  [Fix] _alert_slack_post_message: replace awk -v with ENVIRON pattern for
      channel injection; prevents backslash interpretation in channel names
  [Fix] _alert_html_escape: use printf '%s' output (no trailing newline) to
      match _alert_json_escape, _alert_telegram_escape, _alert_slack_escape
  [New] _alert_deliver_email: validate non-empty recipient at function entry
  [New] _alert_slack_post_message: validate payload_file exists before
      processing; matches _alert_slack_upload validation pattern
  [New] Tests for telegram_document missing chat_id, Reply-To in text-sendmail
      fallback, empty email recipient validation, Slack channel JSON escaping,
      Slack payload_file guard, Slack channel backslash preservation (ENVIRON)
  [Change] README: add ALERT_EMAIL_REPLY_TO to environment variables table,
      add _alert_redact_url to API reference, update version badge and test
      counts
